# Linux Server Monitoring Tool 🚀

A lightweight Linux server monitoring and automation script built using Bash scripting on AWS EC2.

This project helps monitor essential system resources such as CPU usage, memory utilization, disk space, Docker container status, and active users. It is designed as a beginner-friendly DevOps automation project demonstrating Linux administration and server health monitoring concepts.

---

## 📌 Features

* ✅ System uptime monitoring
* ✅ CPU usage monitoring
* ✅ Memory usage monitoring
* ✅ Disk usage monitoring
* ✅ Docker service status check
* ✅ Running Docker containers tracking
* ✅ Logged-in user monitoring
* ✅ Linux server health reporting

---

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

* Linux
* Bash Scripting
* AWS EC2
* Docker
* Git & GitHub

---

## 📂 Project Structure

```bash
linux-server-monitor/
