└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ Setup Instructions

### 1. Clone Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/Vidyasri-Nekuri/linux-server-monitor.git
```

### 2. Navigate to Project

```bash
cd linux-server-monitor
```

### 3. Make Script Executable

```bash
chmod +x monitor.sh
```

### 4. Run Monitoring Script

```bash
./monitor.sh
```

---

## 📊 Monitoring Parameters

The script checks the following system metrics:

| Metric             | Description                             |
| ------------------ | --------------------------------------- |
| System Uptime      | Displays server uptime and load average |
| CPU Usage          | Shows current CPU utilization           |
| Memory Usage       | Displays RAM and swap usage             |
| Disk Usage         | Shows filesystem storage consumption    |
| Docker Status      | Checks whether Docker service is active |
| Running Containers | Lists currently running containers      |
| Logged-in Users    | Displays active user sessions           |

